<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTD/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.pgam.msn-puller.plist

Runs the MSN Partner Hub puller every 15 minutes, using the wrapper
script at ~/.pgam/run-msn-puller.sh which sources credentials from
pgam-intelligence's .env and invokes
   python3 -m agents.etl.msn_insights_etl

Why a LaunchAgent (vs nohup, vs Vercel cron, vs Render):
  - nohup: dies on terminal close / sleep / reboot. Not durable.
  - Vercel cron: can't run Playwright (~300MB Chromium).
  - Render: same — can't host Chromium on the free Python tier.
  - LaunchAgent: starts at login, survives reboot, auto-restarts on
    crash (via KeepAlive), runs while the Mac is awake. The Mac will
    sleep at night; that's fine — the puller's job is just to keep
    MSN data fresh, missing 7-8 hours of overnight pulls is fine
    given MSN's own rolling 24h window covers it.

Load this with:
   launchctl load -w ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.pgam.msn-puller.plist

Unload (disable) with:
   launchctl unload -w ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.pgam.msn-puller.plist

Check status:
   launchctl list | grep com.pgam.msn-puller
   tail -f ~/.pgam/msn-puller.log
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>Label</key>
  <string>com.pgam.msn-puller</string>

  <key>ProgramArguments</key>
  <array>
    <string>/Users/priyeshpatel/.pgam/run-msn-puller.sh</string>
  </array>

  <!-- Every 900 seconds = 15 minutes -->
  <key>StartInterval</key>
  <integer>900</integer>

  <!-- Fire immediately on load so we don't wait 15 min for the first run -->
  <key>RunAtLoad</key>
  <true/>

  <!-- Do NOT auto-restart on completion; this is a periodic one-shot,
       not a daemon. KeepAlive=true would respawn it in a tight loop. -->
  <key>KeepAlive</key>
  <false/>

  <key>StandardOutPath</key>
  <string>/Users/priyeshpatel/.pgam/msn-puller-stdout.log</string>

  <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
  <string>/Users/priyeshpatel/.pgam/msn-puller-stderr.log</string>

  <!-- Don't run if the Mac is on battery and below 50% — be polite
       about energy. Comment out if you want it to run regardless. -->
  <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
  <string>/Users/priyeshpatel/Desktop/pgam-intelligence</string>
</dict>
</plist>
